commit 909fd4108b4ce604f12c46cea9bf93ebb81f9f61
Author: Joris Gillis <joris@yacoda.com>
Date:   Fri May 15 14:54:35 2026 +0200

    Fix Fortran array-descriptor ABI for wasm32-emscripten
    
    Modern Fortran (POINTER, ALLOCATABLE, intrinsics like sum()) crashes
    at runtime because the descriptor struct flang emits uses host-LP64
    widths (i64 elem_len + i64 CFI_index_t per dim) while the runtime
    expects target-wasm32 widths.
    
    Decouple SubscriptValue (function args -> int / i32, matches stock
    RTBuilder.h emission) from CFI_index_t (struct fields -> long long
    / i64, matches stock DescriptorModel.h emission).  Use long long
    rather than int64_t so the typedef does not alias `long` on Linux
    x86-64 LP64 and bypass the existing `Use i32 for long` patch.
    
    4-line reproducer:
      program p
        integer :: a(5) = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
        print *, sum(a)
      end program
    
    Before: RUNTIME_CHECK(TypeCode(CAT, KIND) == x.type() ...) failed at
            reduction-templates.h(90)
    After:  sum: 15

